0. DEFINITIONS

   "The Software" or "Trainfitter" - this addon, including all `.lua` source
   files, asset files (textures, models, sounds, materials), documentation
   (README, this LICENSE), and any other files distributed in this
   repository.

   "Author" - SellingVika, contact sellingvika@gmail.com.

   "Header" - the comment line `-- Made by SellingVika` present in every
   `.lua` source file of this distribution.

   "Fork" - any modified copy of the Software, whether published, shared
   privately, or kept locally.

   "Server" - a Garry's Mod dedicated or listen server running Metrostroi
   Subway Simulator gameplay.

   "Commercial use" - any use where money, paid subscriptions, paid premium
   tiers, donations gated by access, or any form of monetary compensation
   for the Software (or features enabled by it) is involved. Free public
   gameplay on a community server, even one that accepts unrelated
   voluntary donations, is NOT commercial use under this License.

   "Weakened version" - a Fork or modified copy where any of the security
   mechanisms listed in section 3.5 have been disabled, removed, bypassed,
   weakened beyond their official tunable convars, or otherwise rendered
   less effective than in the original.


1. PERMITTED USES (no further permission needed)

   1.1. Install and run Trainfitter on your own Garry's Mod server, free of
        charge, for any non-commercial gameplay purpose.

   1.2. Read, study, audit, and inspect the source code.

   1.3. Submit pull requests, open issues, or send bug reports to the
        original repository.

   1.4. Mention Trainfitter in reviews, video tutorials, blog posts, server
        announcements, public addon lists, or community recommendations,
        provided you credit the Author and link to the original repository.

   1.5. Modify your local copy for personal use on your own server
        (without redistributing the modifications publicly).

   1.6. Tune the Software's behavior using the official convars
        (`trainfitter_*`) - this is exactly what they exist for and does
        NOT count as a "weakened version".


2. PERMITTED WITH CONDITIONS

   2.1. PUBLIC FORKS are allowed only if ALL of the following conditions
        are met simultaneously:

        a. Every original `.lua` file retains the Header
           `-- Made by SellingVika` unchanged. Removing, altering, hiding,
           encoding, or obfuscating the Header is prohibited (section 3.1).

        b. Each Fork or modified `.lua` file gets your authorship line
           IMMEDIATELY AFTER the original Header:

               -- Trainfitter - <filename>.lua
               -- Made by SellingVika
               -- Forked and modified by <your name>

        c. The Fork uses a DISTINCT, derived name. NOT "Trainfitter".
           NOT trivial variations such as "Trainfitter2", "Trainfitter+",
           "TrainfitterRedux", "Trainfitter Pro", etc. Examples of
           acceptable derived names: "Wagonfitter", "MyServerSkinLoader",
           "MetroSkinManager-Custom".

        d. The Fork's README clearly states it is derived from Trainfitter
           by SellingVika, with a working hyperlink to the original
           repository.

        e. The Fork's README contains a CHANGELOG or similar section
           listing what has been modified relative to the original.

        f. The Fork does NOT disable, weaken, bypass, or remove any
           security mechanism of the original (section 3.5). Tuning via
           official convars is fine.

        g. The Fork is NOT distributed via Steam Workshop under the
           original name "Trainfitter".

   2.2. USING PARTS OF THE CODE in unrelated projects is allowed if:

        a. Each reused file or function retains an attribution comment
           naming SellingVika as the original author and Trainfitter as
           the source.

        b. Your project's README, CREDITS, or About screen lists
           Trainfitter and SellingVika with a working link to the original
           repository.

        c. You are NOT using the reused code in a commercial product
           without separate written permission (section 3.4).


3. STRICTLY PROHIBITED

   3.1. REMOVING OR ALTERING THE HEADER.
        Deleting, modifying, masking, encoding, obfuscating, splitting,
        relocating, commenting out, or otherwise rendering the
        `-- Made by SellingVika` line unreadable or absent in ANY `.lua`
        file is prohibited under all circumstances. This applies to the
        original, all Forks, all redistributions, and all derivative
        works in any form.

   3.2. CLAIMING AUTHORSHIP.
        Distributing Trainfitter (modified or not) while presenting
        yourself, your team, or any third party as the original author of
        the Software, its UI, its security scanner, its sandbox, or any
        of its substantial components - is plagiarism and prohibited.

   3.3. REUSING THE NAME "TRAINFITTER".
        Public Forks, derivatives, repackaged versions, server collections,
        Workshop uploads, or any other distribution must NOT use the name
        "Trainfitter" as their own identifier. The name "Trainfitter"
        refers exclusively to this Software by SellingVika.

   3.4. COMMERCIAL USE WITHOUT WRITTEN PERMISSION.
        Selling Trainfitter or any modifications, including but not
        limited to:
          - Reselling as a standalone product;
          - Bundling in paid server packs or "premium" server packages;
          - Gating Trainfitter-provided features behind paid subscriptions
            or VIP tiers;
          - Including in commercial server hosting offerings;
          - Selling support or installation services as the sole product;
          - Using as part of a paid course, paid tutorial bundle, or
            paid asset pack;
        without prior written permission from the Author, is prohibited.

        Free public Garry's Mod servers are explicitly allowed, even if
        they accept unrelated voluntary donations not tied to access.

   3.5. DISTRIBUTING WEAKENED VERSIONS.
        Distributing modified versions ("Forks", repackages, mirrors,
        etc) where any of the following has been disabled, removed,
        weakened beyond official tunable convars, or bypassed - is
        prohibited:
          - The GMA scanner (`Trainfitter.ScanGMA`);
          - The Lua content scanner (`Trainfitter.ValidateSkinLua`,
            `Trainfitter.ValidateMaskLua`);
          - The sandbox (`Trainfitter.ExecSandboxed`);
          - The two-tier path whitelist;
          - The extension whitelist;
          - The bytecode rejection;
          - The instruction limit;
          - The marker requirement;
          - The Material guard;
          - The hook/timer namespacing;
          - The entity proxying;
          - Any rate-limit on net handlers;
          - Any size cap on files, lua content, or addon totals.

        Such a Fork is DANGEROUS to its users and damages the reputation
        of the original. Tuning behavior via the official convars
        (`trainfitter_max_lua_kb`, `trainfitter_sandbox_instr_m`,
        `trainfitter_reject_bytecode`, `trainfitter_allow_full_lua`, etc)
        is fine and is what they exist for.

   3.6. REUPLOADING TO STEAM WORKSHOP UNDER YOUR OWN NAME.
        Publishing Trainfitter (or any modification) on Steam Workshop
        as your own creation is prohibited. Sharing via direct GitHub
        link or your own download service is fine if all other
        conditions of this License are met.

   3.7. USE TO VIOLATE OTHER TERMS.
        Using Trainfitter to violate the Steam Subscriber Agreement,
        Garry's Mod terms of service, Facepunch addon policies, or to
        facilitate any illegal activity on any server, is prohibited.

   3.8. DECEPTIVE LABELING.
        Distributing the Software (or any Fork) with misleading labels
        such as "official", "stable Trainfitter release", "Trainfitter
        successor", "Trainfitter team", or anything implying endorsement
        by or affiliation with SellingVika - is prohibited unless such
        endorsement actually exists and can be proven.


4. ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS

   When publishing a Fork, redistribution, or partial reuse, include
   the following credits in a visible location (typically README, About
   screen, or `credits.txt`):

       Trainfitter by SellingVika
       https://sellingvika.party/
       Original repository: <link to original repository>

   The Header in every `.lua` file already serves this purpose for
   in-code attribution and is mandatory in addition to the above.


